<chapter xml:id="ch-above130" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">

    <title>Course Beyond MA130 Functions</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
        Incoming students with a strong mathematical foundation 
        may take a course above MA130 Functions
        to fulfill their general education mathematics requirement.
        Options include MA165 Calculus I, MA166 Calculus II, MA220
        Calculus III, MA210 Linear Algebra, and MA310 Discrete Mathematics. 
        Information on these courses may be found in the 
        <url href="catalog.rivier.edu/index.php" visual="Rivier University Academic Catalog"/>.
        Students who believe that they are ready to take a course above 
        should contact their <url href="mailto:asktheadvisor@rivier.edu" 
        visual="asktheadvisor@rivier.edu">academic advisor</url> who will  
        facilitate a discussion between you and the Mathematics Program 
        director.
    </p>
  </introduction>
  
  <section xml:id="sec-APandIBscores">
    <title>Advanced Placement and International Baccalaureate scores</title>
    <p>
        Students who have taken an Advanced Placement Test in 
        Calculus or an International Baccalaureate Higher Level 
        Examination may be eligible to receive credit for a mathematics
        course. Once scores are received, students should contact their  
        <url href="mailto:asktheadvisor@rivier.edu" 
        visual="asktheadvisor@rivier.edu">academic advisor</url> to 
        get the credit awarded and discuss schedule and degree plan 
        options. Students who are waiting on their scores are 
        encouraged to enroll in <xref ref="ch-Functions"/> MA130 Functions 
        now to reserve a seat and then to adjust their 
        schedule once scores are available.
    </p>
    
  </section>
</chapter>